.\" -*- nroff -*-
.TH ISISTEST 1 "@DATE@" "NorduGrid ARC @VERSION@" "NorduGrid Users Manual"

.SH NAME

isistest \- ISIS Test

.SH DESCRIPTION

The
.B isistest
command is for managing information stored in the distributed P2P Grid
information cloud of ISIS services.

.SH SYNOPSIS

.B isistest [options]

.SH OPTIONS

.IP "\fB-b\fR, \fB--bootstrap\fR=\fIurl\fR"
the URL of the Bootstrap ISIS
.IP "\fB-i\fR, \fB--isis\fR=\fIurl\fR"
the URL of the ISIS to connect directly
.IP "\fB-n\fR, \fB--neighbors\fR"
get neighbors list from the BootstrapISIS or directly from the ISIS defined
.IP "\fB-m\fR, \fB--method\fR=\fImethod_name\fR"
the method to use on the ISIS
(method_name can be 'Query', 'Register', or 'RemoveRegistration')
.IP "\fB-z\fR, \fB--conffile\fR=\fIfilename\fR"
configuration file (default ~/.arc/client.conf)
.IP "\fB-d\fR, \fB--debug\fR=\fIdebuglevel\fR"
FATAL, ERROR, WARNING, INFO, VERBOSE or DEBUG
.IP "\fB-?\fR, \fB--help\fR"
print help
.LP

.SH USAGE
.IP "isistest -m Query \fIquery_string\fR

.IP "isistest -m Register \fIservice_id\fR,\fIendpoint_reference\fR
[,\fItype\fR[,\fIexpiration_time\fR]]
[\fIservice_id\fR,\fIendpoint_reference\fR[,\fItype\fR
[,\fIexpiration_time\fR]] [...]]"

.IP "isistest -m RemoveRegistration \fIservice_id\fR
[\fIservice_id\fR [...]]"

.SH EXTENDED DESCRIPTION

.TP
The test ISIS client is for the following operations:
.IP "\fBQuery\fR" 4
for querying remote ISIS with an attribute: \fIguery_string\fR
.IP "\fBRegister\fR" 4
for sending test Register messages with one or more set of different number
of arguments.
.RS 4
.IP "\(bu" 4
A ServiceID and an Endpoint reference.
.IP "\(bu" 4
A ServiceID, an Endpoint reference and a Service type.
.IP "\(bu" 4
A ServiceID, an Endpoint reference, a Service type and an
Expiration period.
.RE
.RE

.IP "\fBRemoveRegistration\fR" 4
for sending test RemoveRegistration messages. The arguments are a
list of ServiceIDs to be removed.
.HP
It is also possible to define the BootstrapISIS with the \fB-b\fR or
\fB--bootstrap\fR command line option. The isistest command gets the list
of ISISes from the BootstrapISIS (with the GetISISList operation), then
chooses a random ISIS from that list.
.HP
It's also possible to define the isis url directly
with the \fB-i\fR or \fB--isis\fR option. If there is such an option
defined the GetISISList operation will be skipped even if there is also
a BootstrapISIS defined. (The GetISISList operation will be used in every
other cases impicitly.)
.HP
If there is not a bootstrap either a direct url of an isis given then the first isis url stored in the user configuration will be used directly.
.HP
If \fB-n\fR or \fB--neighbors\fR options are used without any parameters,
then the neighbors of the ISIS or the BootstrapISIS will also be printed.

.SH FILES

.TP
.B ~/.arc/client.conf
Some options can be given default values by specifying them in the
ARC client configuration file. By using the
.B -z
or
.B --conffile
option a different configuration file can be used than the default.

.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES

.TP
.B X509_USER_PROXY
The location of the user's grid proxy file. It should be set only if the
proxy is in a non-standard location.

.TP
.B ARC_LOCATION
The location where ARC is installed can be specified by this variable. If
not specified the install location will be determined from the path to the
command being executed, and if this fails a WARNING will be given stating
the location which will be used.

.TP
.B ARC_PLUGIN_PATH
The location of ARC plugins can be specified by this variable. Multiple
locations can be specified by separating them by : (; in Windows). The
default location is \fB$ARC_LOCATION\fR/lib/arc (\\ in Windows).

.SH EXAMPLES

.IP "isistest -m Register ServiceID1,EPR1"
.IP "isistest -m Register ServiceID1,EPR1,org.nordugrid.tests.echo,PT1M"
.IP "isistest -m Query \[dq]/*\[dq]"
.IP "isistest -m Query /RegEntry/MetaSrcAdv/ServiceID[text()='ServiceID1']"
.IP "isistest -m RemoveRegistration ServiceID1"
.IP "isistest -b https://your.domain.com/infosys -m
RemoveRegistration ServiceID1"
.IP "isistest -i https://your.domain.com/infosys -m Query /RegEntry"

